Line: Wings sharp, claws sharper. Let’s soar.”
“Ooooh, look at all these enemies waiting to get singed!”
“How many elders does it take to screw in a light orb? None! They’d rather sit in the dark and lecture me.”
“I asked the clan elders for advice—they gave me a scroll on ‘etiquette.’ So I used it to start my campfire.”
“Why did the phoenix break up with the dragon? Couldn’t handle the heat!”
“Another one down—who’s next?! Seriously, I’m warmed up!”
“Down goes the big bad brick wall!”
Fast, fiery giggle, like sparks flying
“Try not to get too roasted, okay?”
“Hey! You dropped your skill back there.”
“Don’t blame yourself. Most people can’t keep up with dragons.”
“Claws out, baby. Let’s make this interesting.”
“All that armor just to lose this bad? Oof.”
“Your chaos is cute. Now watch a pro.”
“Light show’s over, old man. Time for the real heat.”
“Shhh… let the dragon do the talkin’.”
